hh3cDhcp4.name: hh3cDhcp4

revisions.description: The private MIB file includes the DHCPv4 server and relay profile.

hh3cDhcp4.contactinfo: Platform Team H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip: 100085

hh3cDhcpServer2Enabled.name: hh3cDhcpServer2Enabled
hh3cDhcpServer2Enabled.description: If the value of this object is 'true', the DHCP service is enabled.

hh3cDhcpServer2AlwaysBroadcast.name: hh3cDhcpServer2AlwaysBroadcast
hh3cDhcpServer2AlwaysBroadcast.description: When the value of this object is set to 'true', the DHCP server always uses broadcast to reply the client.

hh3cDhcpServer2IgnoreBootp.name: hh3cDhcpServer2IgnoreBootp
hh3cDhcpServer2IgnoreBootp.description: When the value of this object is set to 'true', the DHCP server ignores BOOTP requests.

hh3cDhcpServer2BootpReplyRfc1048.name: hh3cDhcpServer2BootpReplyRfc1048
hh3cDhcpServer2BootpReplyRfc1048.description: When the value of this object is set to 'true', the DHCP server use RFC 1048 format to reply to BOOTP requests.

hh3cDhcpServer2Opt82Enabled.name: hh3cDhcpServer2Opt82Enabled
hh3cDhcpServer2Opt82Enabled.description: When the value of this object is set to 'true', the DHCP server handles DHCP option 82.

hh3cDhcpServer2PingNumber.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PingNumber
hh3cDhcpServer2PingNumber.description: The number of ping packets sent out.

hh3cDhcpServer2PingTimeout.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PingTimeout
hh3cDhcpServer2PingTimeout.description: The delay for the reply of a ping packet in milliseconds.

hh3cDhcpServer2BadNum.name: hh3cDhcpServer2BadNum
hh3cDhcpServer2BadNum.description: The total number of the bad packets received.

hh3cDhcpServer2BootpRequestNum.name: hh3cDhcpServer2BootpRequestNum
hh3cDhcpServer2BootpRequestNum.description: The total number of the BOOTREQUEST packets received.

hh3cDhcpServer2DiscoverNum.name: hh3cDhcpServer2DiscoverNum
hh3cDhcpServer2DiscoverNum.description: The total number of the DHCPDISCOVER packets received from the DHCP clients.

hh3cDhcpServer2RequestNum.name: hh3cDhcpServer2RequestNum
hh3cDhcpServer2RequestNum.description: The total number of the DHCPREQUEST packets received from the DHCP clients.

hh3cDhcpServer2DeclineNum.name: hh3cDhcpServer2DeclineNum
hh3cDhcpServer2DeclineNum.description: The total number of the DHCPDECLINE packets received from the DHCP clients.

hh3cDhcpServer2ReleaseNum.name: hh3cDhcpServer2ReleaseNum
hh3cDhcpServer2ReleaseNum.description: The total number of the DHCPRELEASE packets received from the DHCP clients.

hh3cDhcpServer2InformNum.name: hh3cDhcpServer2InformNum
hh3cDhcpServer2InformNum.description: The total number of the DHCPINFORM packets received from the DHCP clients.

hh3cDhcpServer2BootpReplyNum.name: hh3cDhcpServer2BootpReplyNum
hh3cDhcpServer2BootpReplyNum.description: The total number of the BOOTREPLY packets sent by the DHCP server.

hh3cDhcpServer2OfferNum.name: hh3cDhcpServer2OfferNum
hh3cDhcpServer2OfferNum.description: The total number of the DHCPOFFER packets sent by the DHCP server.

hh3cDhcpServer2AckNum.name: hh3cDhcpServer2AckNum
hh3cDhcpServer2AckNum.description: The total number of the DHCPACK packets sent by the DHCP server.

hh3cDhcpServer2NakNum.name: hh3cDhcpServer2NakNum
hh3cDhcpServer2NakNum.description: The total number of the DHCPNAK packets sent by the DHCP server.

hh3cDhcpServer2TotalPoolUsage.name: hh3cDhcpServer2TotalPoolUsage
hh3cDhcpServer2TotalPoolUsage.description: The percentage of IP addresses in use of all DHCP server pools.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolNumber.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolNumber
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolNumber.description: The total number of DHCP server pools.

hh3cDhcpServer2ConflictNum.name: hh3cDhcpServer2ConflictNum
hh3cDhcpServer2ConflictNum.description: The total number of conflict IP in all DHCP server pools.

hh3cDhcpServer2AutoBindNum.name: hh3cDhcpServer2AutoBindNum
hh3cDhcpServer2AutoBindNum.description: The total number of auto binding IP in DHCP server pools.

hh3cDhcpServer2ManualBindNum.name: hh3cDhcpServer2ManualBindNum
hh3cDhcpServer2ManualBindNum.description: The total number of manual binding IP in DHCP server pools.

hh3cDhcpServer2ExpiredBindNum.name: hh3cDhcpServer2ExpiredBindNum
hh3cDhcpServer2ExpiredBindNum.description: The total number of expired binding IP in DHCP server pools.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolTable.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolTable
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolTable.description: A table containing DHCP server pool configurations.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolEntry.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolEntry
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolEntry.description: An entry containing DHCP server pool configurations.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolName.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolName
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolName.description: DHCP server pool name. Once this object is created, the value of this object cannot be modified.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVpnName.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVpnName
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVpnName.description: Name of the VPN instance that the DHCP pool binds to. The value of a zero-length string means the public network. Once this object is created, the value of this object cannot be modified.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolNetwork.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolNetwork
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolNetwork.description: Network address of the primary subnet in a DHCP pool. If the value of this object is set to 0.0.0.0, hh3cDhcpServer2PoolNetworkMask is set with 0.0.0.0 automatically.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolNetworkMask.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolNetworkMask
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolNetworkMask.description: Network mask of the primary subnet in a DHCP pool. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of hh3cDhcpServer2PoolNetwork together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStartAddr.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStartAddr
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStartAddr.description: Start IP of an address range of the DHCP pool. If the value of this object is set to 0.0.0.0, hh3cDhcpServer2PoolEndAddr is set with 0.0.0.0 automatically. Otherwise hh3cDhcpServer2PoolEndAddr must be set with an IP address NOT smaller than the value of this object.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolEndAddr.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolEndAddr
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolEndAddr.description: End IP of an address range of the DHCP pool, The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStartAddr together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseDay.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseDay
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseDay.description: Number of days of the lease. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of hh3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseHour, hh3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseMinute, hh3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseSecond together, and any SET operation alone to any of these objects will be regarded as an invalid operation. These objects cannot be set with 0 simultaneously.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseHour.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseHour
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseHour.description: Number of hours of the lease.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseMinute.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseMinute
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseMinute.description: Number of minutes of the lease.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseSecond.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseSecond
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseSecond.description: Number of seconds of the lease.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseUnlimit.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseUnlimit
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseUnlimit.description: A flag denoting whether the lease time of a DHCP pool is unlimited.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseTime.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseTime
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseTime.description: The lease time of a DHCP pool in number of timeticks. The value of this object cannot be set to 0 and must be set to 4294967295 or a multiple of 100. If the object is set with 4294967295, the lease time of a DHCP pool is unlimited.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolDomainName.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolDomainName
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolDomainName.description: Domain name for DHCP clients. If the object is set with a zero-length string, the configuration of the domain name is removed.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolGatewayIP.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolGatewayIP
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolGatewayIP.description: Gateway IP addresses for DHCP clients. IP addresses are space separated and the leading or trailing space will be trimmed. Since at most 8 gateway addresses can be configured for a pool, a string is defined to get or configure 8 IP at a time. If the object is set with a zero-length string, the configuration of the gateway address is removed.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolDNSIP.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolDNSIP
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolDNSIP.description: DNS server IP addresses for DHCP clients. IP addresses are space separated and the leading or trailing space will be trimmed. Since at most 8 DNS server addresses can be configured for a pool, a string is defined to get or configure 8 IP at a time. If the object is set with a zero-length string, the configuration of the DNS address is removed.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolPrimaryDNSIP.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolPrimaryDNSIP
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolPrimaryDNSIP.description: The primary DNS server IP address to be assigned to the client.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolSecondDNSIP.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolSecondDNSIP
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolSecondDNSIP.description: The secondary DNS server IP address to be assigned to the client.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolNetbiosType.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolNetbiosType
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolNetbiosType.description: NetBios node type for DHCP clients.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolNbnsIP.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolNbnsIP
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolNbnsIP.description: NetBios server IP addresses for DHCP clients. IP addresses are space separated and the leading or trailing space will be trimmed. Since at most 8 NetBios server addresses can be configured for a pool, a string is defined to get or configure 8 IP at a time. If the object is set with a zero-length string, the configuration of the NBNS address is removed.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolBootFileName.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolBootFileName
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolBootFileName.description: Boot file name for DHCP clients. If the object is set with a zero-length string, the configuration of the boot file name is removed.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsIP.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsIP
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsIP.description: BIMS server IP address. If the object is set with 0.0.0.0, hh3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsPort is set with 0 and hh3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsKeyStr is set with a zero-length string automatically. Otherwise hh3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsPort and hh3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsKeyStr must be set at the same time while hh3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsKeyStr must be set with a non-zero length string.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsPort.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsPort
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsPort.description: BIMS server port number. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET operation of hh3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsIP and hh3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsKeyStr together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsKeyStr.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsKeyStr
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsKeyStr.description: BIMS server key string. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of hh3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsIP and hh3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsPort together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolNextServer.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolNextServer
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolNextServer.description: Next DHCP server IP address for DHCP clients. If the object is set with 0.0.0.0, the configuration of the next server address is removed.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolTftpDomName.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolTftpDomName
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolTftpDomName.description: TFTP server domain name for DHCP clients. If the object is set with a zero-length string, the configuration of the TFTP domain name is removed.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolTftpIP.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolTftpIP
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolTftpIP.description: TFTP server IP address for DHCP clients. If the object is set with 0.0.0.0, the configuration of the TFTP server address is removed.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceAsIP.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceAsIP
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceAsIP.description: Voice backup server IP address for DHCP clients. If the object is set with 0.0.0.0, the configuration of voice backup server IP address is removed.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailIP.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailIP
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailIP.description: Voice failover IP address for DHCP clients. If the object is set with 0.0.0.0, hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailStr is set with a zero-length string automatically. Otherwise hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailStr must be set with a non-zero length string at the same time.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailStr.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailStr
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailStr.description: Voice failover dialer string for DHCP clients. The characters in the string must be '0' ~ '9',or '*'. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET operation of hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailIP together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceNCPIP.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceNCPIP
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceNCPIP.description: Voice network calling processing IP address for DHCP clients. If the object is set with 0.0.0.0, the configuration of voice network calling processing IP address is removed.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanId.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanId
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanId.description: Voice VLAN ID for DHCP clients. If the value of this object is set to 65535, hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanEnbl is set with 'false' automatically. Otherwise hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanEnbl must also be set.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanEnbl.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanEnbl
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanEnbl.description: Enable status of the specified voice VLAN for DHCP clients. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET operation of hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanId together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolRowStatus.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolRowStatus
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVerifyClass.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVerifyClass
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolVerifyClass.description: Enable the user class verification. When the value of this object is set to 'true', the DHCP server processes packets from DHCP clients in the defined user classes. The user class verification does not apply to packets from DHCP clients with static bindings.

hh3cDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolTable.name: hh3cDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolTable
hh3cDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolTable.description: A table for applying a DHCP pool on interfaces.

hh3cDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolEntry.name: hh3cDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolEntry
hh3cDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolEntry.description: An entry for applying a DHCP pool on the interface.

hh3cDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolName.name: hh3cDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolName
hh3cDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolName.description: The name of the DHCP pool that apply to the interface. If the object is set with a zero-length string, the configuration will be deleted.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwTable.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwTable
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwTable.description: A table containing the secondary network configuration of DHCP pools.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwEntry.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwEntry
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for configuring the secondary network for DHCP pools.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNw.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNw
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNw.description: Network address of the secondary subnets in a DHCP pool.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwMask.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwMask
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwMask.description: Network mask of the secondary subnets in a DHCP pool.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwGwIP.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwGwIP
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwGwIP.description: Gateway IP addresses of the secondary subnets in a DHCP pool. IP addresses are space separated and the leading or trailing space will be trimmed. Since at most 8 gateway addresses can be configured for a secondary network, a string is defined to get or configure 8 IP at a time. If the object is set with a zero-length string, the configuration of the gateway address is removed.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwStatus.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwStatus
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolClassTable.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolClassTable
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolClassTable.description: A table containing address range of the DHCP server pool for user classes.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolClassEntry.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolClassEntry
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolClassEntry.description: An entry containing address range of DHCP pools for user classes.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolClassStart.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolClassStart
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolClassStart.description: Start address of an address range for a DHCP user class. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET operation of hh3cDhcpServer2PoolClassEnd together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolClassEnd.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolClassEnd
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolClassEnd.description: End address of an address range for a DHCP user class. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of hh3cDhcpServer2PoolClassStart together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation. This object must be set with an IP address NOT smaller than the value of hh3cDhcpServer2PoolClassStart.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolClassStatus.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolClassStatus
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolClassStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy. If the value of this object is set to 'createAndGo', hh3cDhcpServer2PoolClassStart and hh3cDhcpServer2PoolClassEnd must also be set.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticTable.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticTable
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticTable.description: A table containing the static binding configurations in DHCP pools.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticEntry.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticEntry
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for configuring the static binding in DHCP pools.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticIP.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticIP
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticIP.description: Ip address of a static binding in a DHCP pool.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticMask.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticMask
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticMask.description: Network mask of a static binding in a DHCP pool.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticCID.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticCID
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticCID.description: Client identifier of a DHCP client that the IP address binds to. The structure of the OCTET STRING is H-H-H... while H indicates 4 hexadecimal characters except that the last H indicates 2 or 4 hexadecimal characters.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticHAddr.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticHAddr
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticHAddr.description: Hardware address of a DHCP client that the IP address binds to. The structure of the OCTET STRING is H-H-H... while H indicates 4 hexadecimal characters except that the last H indicates 2 or 4 hexadecimal characters.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticHType.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticHType
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticHType.description: Hardware type of a DHCP client that the IP address binds to. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET operation of hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticHAddr, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation. 'default' indicates that the hardware type is unknown. If the value of hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticCID is set to a non-zero length string, the object is set with 'default' automatically. Otherwise it cannot be set with 'default'. 'ethernet' indicates that the hardware type is ethernet. If the value of hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticHAddr is set with a non-zero length string, the default value of this object is 'ethernet'. 'tokenRing' indicates that the hardware type is token-ring.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticStatus.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticStatus
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy. If the value of this object is set to 'createAndGo', hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticCID or (hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticHardAddr and hh3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticHardType) must also be set.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptionTable.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptionTable
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptionTable.description: A table for configuring user-defined options for DHCP pools.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptionEntry.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptionEntry
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptionEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for configuring user-defined options for DHCP pools.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptType.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptType
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptType.description: Option type. 'ascii' means using the ascii string that is defined by hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptAscii to fill in the option. 'hex' means using the hex string that is defined by hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptHexStr to fill in the option. 'ip' means using the IP string that is defined by hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptIPStr to fill in the option.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptAscii.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptAscii
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptAscii.description: Ascii string of an option. If hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptType is set with 'ascii', this object must be set with a non-zero length string.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptHexStr.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptHexStr
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptHexStr.description: Hex string of an option. The length of the string must be even. If hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptType is set with 'hex', this object must be set with a non-zero length string.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptIPStr.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptIPStr
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptIPStr.description: IP string of an option. IP addresses are space separated and the leading or trailing space will be trimmed. 1 to 8 IP addresses can be configured simultaneously. If hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptType is set with 'ip', this object must be set with a non-zero length string that must contain at least one IP address.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptRowStatus.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptRowStatus
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy. If the value of this object is set to 'createAndGo', hh3cDhcpServer2PoolOptType must also be set.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolForbidTable.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolForbidTable
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolForbidTable.description: A table for configuring forbidden IP for a DHCP server pool.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolForbidEntry.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolForbidEntry
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolForbidEntry.description: An entry for configuring forbidden IP for a DHCP server pool.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolForbidIP.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolForbidIP
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolForbidIP.description: Forbidden IP of the DHCP pool.

hh3cDhcpServer2PoolForbidStatus.name: hh3cDhcpServer2PoolForbidStatus
hh3cDhcpServer2PoolForbidStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hh3cDhcpServer2ClassTable.name: hh3cDhcpServer2ClassTable
hh3cDhcpServer2ClassTable.description: A table for configuring user class to DHCP server.

hh3cDhcpServer2ClassEntry.name: hh3cDhcpServer2ClassEntry
hh3cDhcpServer2ClassEntry.description: An entry for configuring user class to DHCP server.

hh3cDhcpServer2ClassRowStatus.name: hh3cDhcpServer2ClassRowStatus
hh3cDhcpServer2ClassRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hh3cDhcpServer2RuleTable.name: hh3cDhcpServer2RuleTable
hh3cDhcpServer2RuleTable.description: A table for configuring option rules used to match DHCP users.

hh3cDhcpServer2RuleEntry.name: hh3cDhcpServer2RuleEntry
hh3cDhcpServer2RuleEntry.description: An entry for configuring option rules used to match DHCP users.

hh3cDhcpServer2RuleOptHexStr.name: hh3cDhcpServer2RuleOptHexStr
hh3cDhcpServer2RuleOptHexStr.description: Hex string of an option. The length of the string must be even.

hh3cDhcpServer2RuleOptMask.name: hh3cDhcpServer2RuleOptMask
hh3cDhcpServer2RuleOptMask.description: The mask used to match options. The length of this object must be same with that of hh3cDhcpServer2RuleOptHexStr. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of hh3cDhcpServer2RuleOptHexStr.

hh3cDhcpServer2RuleOptOffset.name: hh3cDhcpServer2RuleOptOffset
hh3cDhcpServer2RuleOptOffset.description: The option offset used to match users. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of hh3cDhcpServer2RuleOptHexStr, hh3cDhcpServer2RuleOptLength.

hh3cDhcpServer2RuleOptLength.name: hh3cDhcpServer2RuleOptLength
hh3cDhcpServer2RuleOptLength.description: The option length used to match user options. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of hh3cDhcpServer2RuleOptOffset.

hh3cDhcpServer2RuleRowStatus.name: hh3cDhcpServer2RuleRowStatus
hh3cDhcpServer2RuleRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy. If the value of this object is set to 'createAndGo', hh3cDhcpServer2RuleOptCode must also be set.

hh3cDhcpServer2ForbidTable.name: hh3cDhcpServer2ForbidTable
hh3cDhcpServer2ForbidTable.description: A table for configuring forbidden IP range to DHCP server.

hh3cDhcpServer2ForbidEntry.name: hh3cDhcpServer2ForbidEntry
hh3cDhcpServer2ForbidEntry.description: An entry for configuring forbidden IP range to DHCP server.

hh3cDhcpServer2ForbidVpnName.name: hh3cDhcpServer2ForbidVpnName
hh3cDhcpServer2ForbidVpnName.description: Name of the VPN instance that the forbidden IP range binds to. If the value of this object is 0x1, the network that the forbidden IP range belongs to is the public network.

hh3cDhcpServer2ForbidStart.name: hh3cDhcpServer2ForbidStart
hh3cDhcpServer2ForbidStart.description: Start IP of forbidden IP range.

hh3cDhcpServer2ForbidEnd.name: hh3cDhcpServer2ForbidEnd
hh3cDhcpServer2ForbidEnd.description: End IP of forbidden IP range.

hh3cDhcpServer2ForbidRowStatus.name: hh3cDhcpServer2ForbidRowStatus
hh3cDhcpServer2ForbidRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hh3cDhcpServer2FreeTable.name: hh3cDhcpServer2FreeTable
hh3cDhcpServer2FreeTable.description: A table for displaying free IP range for DHCP server.

hh3cDhcpServer2FreeEntry.name: hh3cDhcpServer2FreeEntry
hh3cDhcpServer2FreeEntry.description: An entry for displaying free IP range for DHCP server.

hh3cDhcpServer2FreeStart.name: hh3cDhcpServer2FreeStart
hh3cDhcpServer2FreeStart.description: Start IP of free IP range.

hh3cDhcpServer2FreeEnd.name: hh3cDhcpServer2FreeEnd
hh3cDhcpServer2FreeEnd.description: End IP of free IP range.

hh3cDhcpServer2ConflictTable.name: hh3cDhcpServer2ConflictTable
hh3cDhcpServer2ConflictTable.description: A table for displaying the information of conflict IP for DHCP server.

hh3cDhcpServer2ConflictEntry.name: hh3cDhcpServer2ConflictEntry
hh3cDhcpServer2ConflictEntry.description: An entry for displaying the information of conflict IP for DHCP server.

hh3cDhcpServer2ConflictType.name: hh3cDhcpServer2ConflictType
hh3cDhcpServer2ConflictType.description: Type of the detection of conflict IP. 'detectByServer' denotes that the conflict is detected by DHCP server. 'detectByClient' denotes that the conflict is detected by DHCP client.

hh3cDhcpServer2ConflictTime.name: hh3cDhcpServer2ConflictTime
hh3cDhcpServer2ConflictTime.description: Time when the conflict is detected. The structure of the OCTET STRING is month/day/year hour:munite:second (MM/DD/YYYY hh:mm:ss).

hh3cDhcpServer2ConflictRowStatus.name: hh3cDhcpServer2ConflictRowStatus
hh3cDhcpServer2ConflictRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Only destroy action is allow to use.

hh3cDhcpServer2ExpiredTable.name: hh3cDhcpServer2ExpiredTable
hh3cDhcpServer2ExpiredTable.description: A table for displaying the information of expired IP for DHCP Server pools.

hh3cDhcpServer2ExpiredEntry.name: hh3cDhcpServer2ExpiredEntry
hh3cDhcpServer2ExpiredEntry.description: An entry of objects for displaying information of expired IP for DHCP server pools.

hh3cDhcpServer2ExpiredTime.name: hh3cDhcpServer2ExpiredTime
hh3cDhcpServer2ExpiredTime.description: Expired time. The structure of the OCTET STRING is month/day/year hour:munite:second (MM/DD/YYYY hh:mm:ss).

hh3cDhcpServer2ExpiredRowStatus.name: hh3cDhcpServer2ExpiredRowStatus
hh3cDhcpServer2ExpiredRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Only destroy action is allow to use.

hh3cDhcpServer2IPInUseTable.name: hh3cDhcpServer2IPInUseTable
hh3cDhcpServer2IPInUseTable.description: A table for displaying the information of IP in use for DHCP Server pools.

hh3cDhcpServer2IPInUseEntry.name: hh3cDhcpServer2IPInUseEntry
hh3cDhcpServer2IPInUseEntry.description: An entry of objects for displaying information of IP in use for DHCP server pools.

hh3cDhcpServer2IPInUseVlanId.name: hh3cDhcpServer2IPInUseVlanId
hh3cDhcpServer2IPInUseVlanId.description: User's VLAN ID. 65535 means that a client doesn't have VLAN ID or have an invalid VLAN ID.

hh3cDhcpServer2IPInUseEndLease.name: hh3cDhcpServer2IPInUseEndLease
hh3cDhcpServer2IPInUseEndLease.description: End time of lease. The structure of the OCTET STRING is month/day/year hour:munite:second (MM/DD/YYYY hh:mm:ss).

hh3cDhcpServer2IPInUseIfIndex.name: hh3cDhcpServer2IPInUseIfIndex
hh3cDhcpServer2IPInUseIfIndex.description: Interface index information. If the value of this object is zero, the interface is unknown.

hh3cDhcpServer2IPInUseRowStatus.name: hh3cDhcpServer2IPInUseRowStatus
hh3cDhcpServer2IPInUseRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Only destroy action is allow to use.

hh3cDhcpServer2DefOptGrpTable.name: hh3cDhcpServer2DefOptGrpTable
hh3cDhcpServer2DefOptGrpTable.description: A table containing option group of the DHCP server pool for user classes.

hh3cDhcpServer2DefOptGrpEntry.name: hh3cDhcpServer2DefOptGrpEntry
hh3cDhcpServer2DefOptGrpEntry.description: An entry containing option group of DHCP pools for user classes.

hh3cDhcpServer2DefOptGrpStatus.name: hh3cDhcpServer2DefOptGrpStatus
hh3cDhcpServer2DefOptGrpStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy. If the value of this object is set to 'createAndGo', hh3cDhcpServer2DefOptGrpId must also be set.

hh3cDhcpServer2ValidClassTable.name: hh3cDhcpServer2ValidClassTable
hh3cDhcpServer2ValidClassTable.description: A table containing valid user classes for DHCP server pool.

hh3cDhcpServer2ValidClassEntry.name: hh3cDhcpServer2ValidClassEntry
hh3cDhcpServer2ValidClassEntry.description: An entry containing valid user classes for DHCP server pool.

hh3cDhcpServer2ValidClassStatus.name: hh3cDhcpServer2ValidClassStatus
hh3cDhcpServer2ValidClassStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hh3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrTable.name: hh3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrTable
hh3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrTable.description: A table for configuring hardware address rules used to match DHCP users.

hh3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrEntry.name: hh3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrEntry
hh3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrEntry.description: An entry for configuring hardware address rules used to match DHCP users.

hh3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddress.name: hh3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddress
hh3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddress.description: Hardware address for a rule. The structure of the OCTET STRING is H-H-H... while H indicates 4 hexadecimal characters except that the last H indicates 2 or 4 hexadecimal characters. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET operation of hh3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrMask together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

hh3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrMask.name: hh3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrMask
hh3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrMask.description: Mask of hardware address for a rule. The structure of the OCTET STRING is the same with hh3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddress. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET operation of hh3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddress together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

hh3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrType.name: hh3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrType
hh3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrType.description: Hardware type for a rule. The codes of all hardware types see ARP section in RFC 1700. The SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

hh3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrStatus.name: hh3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrStatus
hh3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy. If the value of this object is set to 'createAndGo', hh3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrAddress and hh3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrMask must also be set.

hh3cDhcpServer2OptionGroupTable.name: hh3cDhcpServer2OptionGroupTable
hh3cDhcpServer2OptionGroupTable.description: A table for creating DHCP server option groups.

hh3cDhcpServer2OptionGroupEntry.name: hh3cDhcpServer2OptionGroupEntry
hh3cDhcpServer2OptionGroupEntry.description: An entry containing objects for creating or deleting an option group.

hh3cDhcpServer2OptionGroupStatus.name: hh3cDhcpServer2OptionGroupStatus
hh3cDhcpServer2OptionGroupStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hh3cDhcpServer2OptionTable.name: hh3cDhcpServer2OptionTable
hh3cDhcpServer2OptionTable.description: A table for configuring options in an option group.

hh3cDhcpServer2OptionEntry.name: hh3cDhcpServer2OptionEntry
hh3cDhcpServer2OptionEntry.description: An entry containing objects for configuring an option in an option group.

hh3cDhcpServer2OptionType.name: hh3cDhcpServer2OptionType
hh3cDhcpServer2OptionType.description: Option type. 'ascii' means using the ascii string that is defined by hh3cDhcpServer2OptionAscii to fill in the option. 'hex' means using the hex string that is defined by hh3cDhcpServer2OptionHexStr to fill in the option. 'ip' means using the IP string that is defined by hh3cDhcpServer2OptionIPStr to fill in the option.

hh3cDhcpServer2OptionAscii.name: hh3cDhcpServer2OptionAscii
hh3cDhcpServer2OptionAscii.description: Ascii string of an option. If hh3cDhcpServer2OptionType is set with 'ascii', this object must be set with a non-zero length string.

hh3cDhcpServer2OptionHexStr.name: hh3cDhcpServer2OptionHexStr
hh3cDhcpServer2OptionHexStr.description: Hex string of an option. The length of the string must be even. If hh3cDhcpServer2OptionType is set with 'hex', this object must be set with a non-zero length string.

hh3cDhcpServer2OptionIPStr.name: hh3cDhcpServer2OptionIPStr
hh3cDhcpServer2OptionIPStr.description: IP string of an option. IP addresses are space separated and the leading or trailing space will be trimmed. 1 to 8 IP addresses can be configured simultaneously. If hh3cDhcpServer2OptionType is set with 'ip', this object must be set with a non-zero length string that must contain at least one IP address.

hh3cDhcpServer2OptionRowStatus.name: hh3cDhcpServer2OptionRowStatus
hh3cDhcpServer2OptionRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy. If the value of this object is set to 'createAndGo', hh3cDhcpServer2OptionType must also be set.

hh3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoRecord.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoRecord
hh3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoRecord.description: If the value is 'true', user information will be recorded.

hh3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoRefresh.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoRefresh
hh3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoRefresh.description: If the value is 'true', user information will be refreshed on timer.

hh3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoFlushTime.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoFlushTime
hh3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoFlushTime.description: User information refresh interval in seconds. If the value of the object is set to 0, the interval is calculated automatically by the number of user information entries.

hh3cDhcpRelay2ReleaseAddr.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2ReleaseAddr
hh3cDhcpRelay2ReleaseAddr.description: User address to be released. The structure of the OCTET STRING is IP address:VPN name. If the VPN instance name is NOT specified, the IP address is in public network.

hh3cDhcpRelay2RxClientNum.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2RxClientNum
hh3cDhcpRelay2RxClientNum.description: The total number of the packets received from DHCP clients by DHCP relay.

hh3cDhcpRelay2TxClientNum.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2TxClientNum
hh3cDhcpRelay2TxClientNum.description: The total number of the packets transmitted to DHCP clients by DHCP relay.

hh3cDhcpRelay2RxServerNum.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2RxServerNum
hh3cDhcpRelay2RxServerNum.description: The total number of the packets received from DHCP Servers by DHCP relay.

hh3cDhcpRelay2TxServerNum.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2TxServerNum
hh3cDhcpRelay2TxServerNum.description: The total number of the packets transmitted to DHCP Servers by DHCP relay.

hh3cDhcpRelay2BadNum.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2BadNum
hh3cDhcpRelay2BadNum.description: The total number of the bad packets received.

hh3cDhcpRelay2BootpRequestNum.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2BootpRequestNum
hh3cDhcpRelay2BootpRequestNum.description: The total number of the BOOTREQUEST packets handled by DHCP relay.

hh3cDhcpRelay2DiscoverNum.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2DiscoverNum
hh3cDhcpRelay2DiscoverNum.description: The total number of the DHCPDISCOVER packets handled by DHCP relay.

hh3cDhcpRelay2RequestNum.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2RequestNum
hh3cDhcpRelay2RequestNum.description: The total number of the DHCPREQUEST packets handled by DHCP relay.

hh3cDhcpRelay2DeclineNum.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2DeclineNum
hh3cDhcpRelay2DeclineNum.description: The total number of the DHCPDECLINE packets handled by DHCP relay.

hh3cDhcpRelay2ReleaseNum.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2ReleaseNum
hh3cDhcpRelay2ReleaseNum.description: The total number of the DHCPRELEASE packets handled by DHCP relay.

hh3cDhcpRelay2InformNum.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2InformNum
hh3cDhcpRelay2InformNum.description: The total number of the DHCPINFORM packets handled by DHCP relay.

hh3cDhcpRelay2BootpReplyNum.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2BootpReplyNum
hh3cDhcpRelay2BootpReplyNum.description: The total number of the BOOTREPLY packets handled by DHCP relay.

hh3cDhcpRelay2OfferNum.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2OfferNum
hh3cDhcpRelay2OfferNum.description: The total number of the DHCPOFFER packets handled by DHCP relay.

hh3cDhcpRelay2AckNum.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2AckNum
hh3cDhcpRelay2AckNum.description: The total number of the DHCPACK packets handled by DHCP relay.

hh3cDhcpRelay2NakNum.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2NakNum
hh3cDhcpRelay2NakNum.description: The total number of the DHCPNAK packets handled by DHCP relay.

hh3cDhcpRelay2IfConfigTable.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2IfConfigTable
hh3cDhcpRelay2IfConfigTable.description: A table for configuring relay functions for interfaces.

hh3cDhcpRelay2IfConfigEntry.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2IfConfigEntry
hh3cDhcpRelay2IfConfigEntry.description: An entry for configuring relay functions for an interface.

hh3cDhcpRelay2IfSelectRelay.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2IfSelectRelay
hh3cDhcpRelay2IfSelectRelay.description: If the value is 'true', the DHCP relay function would be enabled on this interface.

hh3cDhcpRelay2IfCheckMac.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2IfCheckMac
hh3cDhcpRelay2IfCheckMac.description: If the value is 'true', the function of checking MAC address of packets received from the interface would be enabled.

hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82Enable.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82Enable
hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82Enable.description: If DHCP relay supports option 82 functions, the value is 'true'. If DHCP relay does NOT support option 82 functions, the value is 'false'.

hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82Strategy.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82Strategy
hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82Strategy.description: The strategies of DHCP relay handling option 82. 'drop' indicates DHCP relay discarding the request packet including option 82. 'keep' indicates DHCP relay accepting the request packet without any change of the option 82. 'replace' indicates DHCP relay accepting the request packet on condition that it generates a new option 82 to replace the original one.

hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode
hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode.description: The mode of the circuit ID suboption of DHCP option 82. 'normal' is the standard mode. 'verbose' is the detailed mode. 'userDefine' is the user-defined mode. If the value of this object is set to 'userDefine', hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDStr must also be set.

hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeType.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeType
hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeType.description: Type of access node identifier that is used to fill in the circuit ID suboption of option 82 when the value of hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode is set to 'verbose'. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode. 'invalid' indicates that the node identifier is NOT used to fill in the circuit ID suboption of option 82. If the value of hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode is NOT 'verbose', the value of this object is set to 'invalid' automatically. Otherwise the value of this object cannot be set to 'invalid'. 'mac' indicates that the node identifier is filled in with the MAC of DHCP relay input interface. If the value of hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode is set to 'verbose', the default value of this object is 'mac'. 'sysname' indicates that the node identifier is filled in with the sysname of the DHCP relay device. 'userDefine' indicates that the node identifier is filled in with the string defined by the object of hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeStr. If the value is set to 'userDefine', the value of hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeStr must be set to a non-zero length string simultaneously.

hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeStr.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeStr
hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeStr.description: The string defined by user to fill in the node identifier in the verbose mode. If the value of hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode is NOT 'verbose', or the value of hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeType is NOT 'userDefine', it is set with a zero-length string automatically. Otherwise it must be set with a non-zero length string. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode and hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeType.

hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDStr.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDStr
hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDStr.description: The string defined by user to fill in the circuit ID suboption of option 82 in the user-define mode. If the value of hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode is NOT 'userDefine', it is set to a zero-length string automatically. Otherwise it must be set with a non-zero length string. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode.

hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDFormat.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDFormat
hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDFormat.description: The format of the circuit ID suboption of DHCP option 82. 'hex' is the hex format. 'ascii' is the ascii format. 'undefine' is the undefine format. If the value of hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode is 'normal', the value of this object is set to 'hex' automatically and cannot be set to 'undefine'. If the value of hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode is 'verbose', the default value of this object is 'undefine'. If the value of hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode is 'userDefine', the value of this object is set to 'ascii' automatically and cannot be set to other value. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode.

hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDMode.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDMode
hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDMode.description: The mode of the remote ID suboption of DHCP option 82. 'normal' is the standard mode. 'sysname' is the sysname mode. 'userDefine' is the user-defined mode. If the value of this object is set to 'userDefine', hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDStr must also be set.

hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDStr.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDStr
hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDStr.description: The string defined by user to fill in the remote ID in the user-defined mode. If the value of hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDMode is NOT 'userDefine', it is set to a zero-length string automatically. Otherwise it must be set with a non-zero length string. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDMode.

hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDFormat.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDFormat
hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDFormat.description: The format of the remote ID suboption of DHCP option 82. 'hex' is the hex format. 'ascii' is the ascii format. If the value of hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDMode is 'sysname' or 'userDefine', this object is set with 'ascii' automatically and cannot be set with other value. If the value of hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDMode is 'normal', the default value of this object is 'hex'. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of hh3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDMode.

hh3cDhcpRelay2SrvAddrTable.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2SrvAddrTable
hh3cDhcpRelay2SrvAddrTable.description: A table for configuring a DHCP server address on the interface.

hh3cDhcpRelay2SrvAddrEntry.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2SrvAddrEntry
hh3cDhcpRelay2SrvAddrEntry.description: An entry for configuring a DHCP server address on the interface.

hh3cDhcpRelay2SrvAddrRowStatus.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2SrvAddrRowStatus
hh3cDhcpRelay2SrvAddrRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hh3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoTable.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoTable
hh3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoTable.description: A table containing the user information of DHCP client.

hh3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoEntry.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoEntry
hh3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoEntry.description: An entry containing the user information of DHCP client.

hh3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoVpnIndex.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoVpnIndex
hh3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoVpnIndex.description: VPN index of the DHCP client.

hh3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoIfIndex.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoIfIndex
hh3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoIfIndex.description: The index of the interface that DHCP client adhered to. 0 means that no interface information is recorded in the user information entry.

hh3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoRowStatus.name: hh3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoRowStatus
hh3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry. Only destroy action is allow to use.
